BEAVER CREEK - http://www.beavercreek.com

HAVE THE POWDER ALL TO YOURSELF!
With almost 2 FEET of snow this week, Beaver Creek is
opening more and more terrain every day. Larkspur Bowl
opened last Saturday to an incredible day of powder and blue
skies. With more terrain and less people, you'll find the
powder all to yourself. Start taking advantage of Colorado's
best kept secret. Beaver Creek is getting ready to open Grouse
Mountain, a virtual powder paradise in waiting. Check out
Beaver Creek online for the latest mountain statistics.
Remember, the mountain is only half the experience. Enjoy a
fabulous dinner in the village. Our restaurant pick of the week
is Toscanini. For an upbeat, delicious Italian experience
call 970-845-5590.

PINES LODGE
$129 per lodge room
Rate valid 12/11-12/17/01
Call 1-888-414-6238 for reservations.

SEASONS AT AVON
$143 per two-bedroom condominium
Rate valid 12/11-12/17/01
Call 1-888-414-6238 for reservations.

********************************************
KEYSTONE - http://www.keystoneresort.com

More terrain is scheduled to open at Keystone including The
Outback for expert skiing only on Saturday!  There will be
17 lifts running and for the free riders, there will be hits
at the top of Flying Dutchmen.  And if you can't get in enough
during the day, night skiing will be available 7 days a week
starting Friday!  Take a pre-holiday holiday this weekend
at and get yourself in a holly-jolly mood.  What could be
better after a day of great skiing and riding than all the
things that make the holidays feel so special - lights, ice
skating, fireplaces, decorations, and holiday cheer.

KEYSTONE INN:  $89 per hotel room
MOUNTAIN HOUSE: $109 per slopeside studio
FOREST/ASPEN RIDGE: $219 per 2-bdrm deluxe condominium

Call 1-800-468-4991 for reservations and more information.

*Rates valid 12/11-12/17/01.  Each reservation includes FREE
Mountain Passports - your access passes to the guided mountain
tours, ski tuning clinics, wine tasting, yoga and more!  Based
on availability/inventory.  Not valid for group or conference
stays.

*************************************************
EARLY SEASON COLORADO CARD PRICING

Don't forget, if you ski or ride before December 21, 2001,
you'll earn 5,000 bonus PEAKS points - that's halfway to a
free lift ticket or other great reward.  Adult Colorado Card
holders ski or ride for just $29 per day, and kids ski for $15
per day at Keystone and Breckenridge.  At Vail and Beaver
Creek, adults ski or ride for $39 per day and children ski for
$19 per day.  All prices listed are valid now through
December 21, 2001.

